1 (2) the difference between:
2 (A) The fair market value of the property immediately before the fire
3 event; or
4 (B) the fair market value of the property immediately after the fire
5 event.
6 (e) Pursuant to K.S.A. 60-3701(e) 60-3702(e), and amendments
7 thereto, punitive damages awarded under a fire claim brought under
8 subsection (c) pursuant to this section shall not exceed $5,000,000.
9 Sec. 2. (a) On or before July 31, 2026, the state corporation
10 commission shall provide training opportunities convene a workshop to
11 assess wildfire risk and mitigation. Such trainings workshop shall provide
12 a forum for the presentation and discussion of the following
13 information:
14 (a)(1) General wildfire risks in the state;
15 (b)(2) utility readiness to mitigate wildfire risks;
16 (c)(3) risk mitigation strategies and approaches; and
17 (d)(4) cost recovery treatment for wildfire mitigation costs, including
18 investments and expenses.
19 (b) If determined necessary by the state corporation commission,
20 the commission may open a general investigation or convene additional
21 workshops to further assess utility wildfire risk and mitigation.
22 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
23 publication in the statute book.

